sentences: In 2016, Moor Mother released a studio album, Fetish Bones, on Don Giovanni Records.
In 2017, she released a studio album, The Motionless Present, on The Vinyl Factory.
She served as one of the guest curators at the 2018 Le Guess Who? music festival.
In 2019, she released Analog Fluids of Sonic Black Holes.
From Fall 2021, Ayewa serves as assistant professor at the University of Southern California's Thornton School of Music.

She met the quintet's members through musical and activist endeavors: bassist Luke Stewart shared bills with her band the Mighty Paradocs; saxophonist Keir Neuringer worked with Books Through Bars, whose events Ayewa has emceed; and the trio of Ayewa, Stewart, and Neuringer was followed by the duo of trumpeter Aquiles Navarro and drummer Tcheser Holmes at a 2015 Musicians Against Brutality event following the shooting of Akai Gurley.
In 2017, she released a studio album, The Motionless Present, on The Vinyl Factory.
The same year, she released a collaborative EP with Mental Jewelry, titled Crime Waves, on Don Giovanni Records.

The group performed in the inaugural season of the Kennedy Center's "Direct Current" contemporary culture showcase, and their releases have been included in best-of lists in Magnet, NPR Music, The Quietus, and Stereogum's "20 Best Jazz Albums Of The 2010s".
